1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,237
(John 1:1): 'In the beginning was the word.

2
00:00:04,187 --> 00:00:07,012
Theologians talk of the eternal Word.

3
00:00:07,012 --> 00:00:11,037
God never spoke but one word, and that is still unspoken.

4
00:00:11,037 --> 00:00:13,187
The explanation is this.

5
00:00:13,187 --> 00:00:19,287
The eternal Word is the logos of the Father which is his only begotten Son our Lord Jesus Christ.

6
00:00:19,287 --> 00:00:23,787
In him he pronounces all creatures without beginning and without end.

7
00:00:23,787 --> 00:00:28,600
This accounts for the Word remaining unborn, for it never came out of the Father.

8
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:31,775
This Word is to be known in fourfold guise.

9
00:00:31,775 --> 00:00:34,962
First, on the altar in the priest’s hands.

10
00:00:34,962 --> 00:00:41,600
There it is ours to know and love the eternal Word as we, in his eternal Word, appear to the heavenly Father.

11
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:46,512
Secondly, we know the eternal Word as expounded by doctors from the chair.

12
00:00:46,512 --> 00:00:53,362
We receive it in their person; like water flowing in a channel, so does the eternal Word flow through its teachers.

13
00:00:53,362 --> 00:01:02,725
We should pay no heed to any shortcomings in the doctor: we must fix our gaze on the eternal Word in him, as it comes pouring eternally out of the ground of itself.

14
00:01:02,725 --> 00:01:16,750
Thirdly, we can recognise the eternal Word in our Lord’s friends who, having followed this eternal Word, have gotten proof of it in life eternal, and also those that follow it in time, such, namely, as are quick in our Lord Jesus Christ.

15
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:25,925
Fourthly, we have the eternal Word as spoken in the virgin soul by God himself; wordlessly, to wit, since the soul is not able to express him.

16
00:01:25,925 --> 00:01:32,950
I would have you know that the eternal Word is being born within the soul, its very self, no less, unceasingly.

17
00:01:32,950 --> 00:01:38,362
I tell you, the soul knows the eternal Word better than all the doctors can expound it.

18
00:01:38,362 --> 00:01:44,237
What we can express is all too little, so for the nonce she is bearing the eternal Word in mind.

19
00:01:44,237 --> 00:01:57,912
According to the masters we ought by rights to go to school where the Holy Ghost is teacher; and know, where he is teacher and is bound to be, there he finds students properly equipped to profit by his lofty teaching which issues from out the Father’s heart.

20
00:01:57,912 --> 00:02:06,387
So the soul has, if she will, the Father and the Son and Holy Ghost: she goes flowing into the one where naked in naked is revealed to her.

21
00:02:06,387 --> 00:02:13,450
Our masters say that no one can attain to this so long as he retains of nether things as much as a needle-point can carry.

22
00:02:13,450 --> 00:02:19,287
Into the naked Godhead none may get except he be as naked as he was when he was spilt from God.

23
00:02:19,287 --> 00:02:27,225
The masters say, giving us wise counsel, that leaving God his glory we ought to get all things direct from him and not from creatures.

24
00:02:27,225 --> 00:02:34,012
We shall leave God his glory by leaving him to work just how he will and when he will, we staying idle and free.

25
00:02:34,012 --> 00:02:37,112
For we must see that God does all for the best.

26
00:02:37,112 --> 00:02:42,962
And so I trow it lies with us, so far as it is in us, to help God to preserve his glory.

27
00:02:42,962 --> 00:02:48,287
A master says, Little recks the king of those of his retainers who perform the drudgery.

28
00:02:48,287 --> 00:02:53,237
He notices the ones about his privy chambers and gratifies their every want.

29
00:02:53,237 --> 00:03:00,587
God does the same with his chosen friends, the intimates of his mysterious privacy: he never turns a deaf ear to their prayer.

30
00:03:00,587 --> 00:03:08,250
Withal the masters do affirm that numbers go to heaven who know no more of God on earth than, as it were, of sun in forest gloom.

31
00:03:08,250 --> 00:03:14,037
Desiring this supremely it rests with us to compass it by practice and by strength of will.

32
00:03:14,037 --> 00:03:14,925
Amen.
